{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/gettingstarted"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"roleHeading":"API Collection","title":"Getting Started with Spooktacular","role":"collectionGroup"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create your first macOS virtual machine in minutes."}],"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Core-Types","title":"Core Types","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineBundle","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineSpecification","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachine"]},{"anchor":"Configuration","title":"Configuration","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineConfiguration","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/ProvisioningMode"]},{"anchor":"Guides","title":"Guides","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CLIReference","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GitHubActionsGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide"]}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Guides","title":"Guides","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CLIReference","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GitHubActionsGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/OpenClawGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Spooktacular runs macOS virtual machines on Apple Silicon using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Apple’s Virtualization framework. You interact with it through the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"GUI app or the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook"},{"type":"text","text":" CLI — both backed by the same"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" library. A Kubernetes operator is planned for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a future release."}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You need an Apple Silicon Mac (M1 or later) running"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"macOS 14.0 (Sonoma) or later. Each VM requires at least 20 GB of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"free disk space and 4 CPU cores (see"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineSpecification\/minimumCPUCount","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":")."}]}],"name":"Important","type":"aside","style":"important"},{"anchor":"Creating-a-VM-with-the-CLI","text":"Creating a VM with the CLI","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Install Spooktacular and create a VM from the latest compatible IPSW:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"bash","code":["# Install via Homebrew","brew install --cask spooktacular","","# Create from the latest compatible IPSW","spook create my-vm --from-ipsw latest","","# Or specify custom hardware resources","spook create runner --cpu 8 --memory 16 --disk 100"],"type":"codeListing"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"IPSW installation takes 10–20 minutes per VM. For faster","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"deployment, create a base VM once, then use ","type":"text"},{"code":"spook clone","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"instant copies.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note"},{"anchor":"Creating-a-VM-with-the-GUI","text":"Creating a VM with the GUI","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Open Spooktacular.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Click the ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"+","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" button or press "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Cmd+N"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Enter a name and adjust hardware settings.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Click "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Create","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The app downloads the latest compatible macOS IPSW and installs it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"into a new VM bundle."}]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Managing VMs","anchor":"Managing-VMs"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook"},{"type":"text","text":" CLI for day-to-day VM management:"}]},{"syntax":"bash","type":"codeListing","code":["# List all VMs","spook list","","# Start a VM (opens display window)","spook start my-vm","","# Start headless (for CI runners and servers)","spook start my-vm --headless","","# Clone instantly using APFS copy-on-write","spook clone my-vm runner-01","","# Show VM configuration","spook get my-vm","","# Delete a VM permanently","spook delete my-vm --force"]},{"name":"Important","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple Silicon supports a maximum of 2 concurrent VMs"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"per host. Attempting to start a third VM fails. See"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CapacityCheck"},{"type":"text","text":" for details."}]}],"style":"important"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Provisioning with User-Data Scripts","anchor":"Provisioning-with-User-Data-Scripts"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Automate VM setup by running a shell script after boot via SSH:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["spook start runner --headless \\","    --user-data ~\/setup.sh \\","    --provision ssh \\","    --ssh-user admin"],"syntax":"bash"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ssh"},{"text":" mode waits for the VM to boot, discovers its IP, connects","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"via SSH, and executes your script with real-time output streaming.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Disk-inject provisioning (zero-touch, no SSH required) is in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"progress. See ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/ProvisioningMode","isActive":true},{"text":" for provisioning strategies and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"doc:Provisioning","type":"text"},{"text":" for detailed guidance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"anchor":"EC2-Mac-Setup","type":"heading","text":"EC2 Mac Setup"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Deploy Spooktacular on AWS EC2 Mac instances to double your CI"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"capacity. Install Spooktacular, create VMs from IPSW, clone"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"configured bases, and start runners with SSH provisioning."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"See ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" for detailed EC2 Mac configuration.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A Kubernetes operator (MacOSVM CRD) is planned for a future"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"release. See "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide","isActive":true},{"text":" for the planned architecture.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note"}]}],"kind":"article","references":{"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/VirtualMachineBundle":{"title":"VirtualMachineBundle","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"VirtualMachineBundle"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A virtual machine bundle stored on disk."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineBundle","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/virtualmachinebundle","type":"topic","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text",